column2: Water cleared up after rain on 5/1/87.
Windy and rainy for several days.
Air temperature has been 90+ for four days.
Dry.  Green specs in water.  Heavy weekend traffic.
Very little algae so far this year.
Secchi reading = 22+ ft -- ran out of rope at 22'.
Secchi reading = 22+ ft -- ran out of rope at 22 ft.- 1/2 " rain on 6/12.
Secchi reading 22+ ft.  Ran out of rope at 22 ft.
Excess rain + runoff.  Water slow to clear up.
Unusual amount of algae in shallows this past week.
There has been no rain between 7/22-7/30.
6" of rain on 8/17- 1.7" of rain on 8/25- ran off was heavy.  The rain gauge reading from 8/1-8/27 was 7.8".  Water level: Up approximately 4"
The rain gauge reading from 8/28-9/25 was 1.1".
The rain gauge reading from 9/25-10/15 is 0.6".
About 5 1/2 inches of rain in the past week.
Heavy rainfall.  The rain gauge reading from 8/27-9/25 is 8.6 inches.
IF TP  more than  0.2 RUN AT HIGH LEVEL
The rain gauge reading from 6/19-7/29 is 3.37 inches.
IF TP  more than  0.2 RUN AT HIGH LEVEL
Muskie tournament on 8/15 and 8/16- big boats!  rain gauge reading from 7/30-8/18 is 0.66 inches.
IF TP  more than  0.2 RUN AT HIGH LEVEL
IF TP  more than  0.2 RUN AT HIGH LEVEL
Very heavy rainfall throughout the period.
Numerous downpours during the period.  Water level: up 3"
100% cloud cover- moderate amount of filamentous algae on shore line.
Water getting very green- lots of weeds.
Cloudy- SW winds- getting more weeds.
Rain gauge reading from 5/15/97 to 6/10/97=0.2 inches.  Filamentous algae showing up.  Weed growth getting a good start.
Hard rain last three days.  Lots of weeds.  Algae not too bad today.  Rain gauge reading from 6/11 to 7/15 = 7.20 inches.
Cloudy and hazy.  Rain gauge reading from 8/12 to 9/8 = 6.12 inches.
Strong westerly winds for 2 weeks. 2.65" rain since 5-1-99.
Started to rain while sampling. 6.21" rain since 5-11-99.
1 1/2" rain on 5/7.  Windy and partly cloudy.
Sunny- 75 degrees - after 9 days of 90+ temps.  No recent rains.
Sunny.  Past 5 days very hot.  Several very windy.
Sunny- very humid- 6 days in a row of 90+ degree temps.
The weather today is cloudy- windy- temps. in low 70's.
The sky was partly cloudy.  Temperature 48 degrees.
Partly cloudy- after several hot- humid days.  Very windy many days.
Sunny day.  Several days of rainy weather recently.
Party cloudy-very cool spring-no 80's yet- lake has suspended algae but water is clear Cool spring (no 80s yet)-lake has suspended algae but water is clear
Very dry- creek not even running-cool spring
Still very dry--today is breezy with surface ripples

Lake is very low-lowest I've seen it in  the 47 years I have been on it.  Cool dry summer with lots of wind.  Since we are weekenders- we have had a difficult time finding calm times to get on the lake to do the data collecting.
Very warm early spring-lake looks more like mid August than June.  Been dry.
With the creek running well and the recent rain the lake clarity looks much better.  No itch and minimal algae
Been breezy and sometimes windy but had to do the readings since we will be gonew for a couple weeks
Been a very cool early summer with lots of rain.  May was very cool and cloudy most of the month.  We have had two very hot days this week.
Mostly sunny day but breezy 8-10" chop
Very hot week-bit overcasxt slight chop on the water
It has been sunny and very hot the past seevral days- not rain.  It has been a very - very busy lake weekend due the fourth of July holiday.
Lake looks clear but choppy in open area- Clear skies
Partly cloudy day.  We have had some cool nights (50s)
IT HAS BEEN A VERY EARLY SPRING AND HOT EARLY SUMMER.  TODAY IS WINDY AND LAKE ISW CHOPPY- NOSUN
CLEAR BUT WINDY AND CHOPPY- LAKE LOOKS GREAT FOR THE WEEK OF THE 4TH
Partly cloudy-a bit windy and choppy
Overcast-no sun.  Slight ripples.  Busy- busy boating weekend.  Lots of floating cut plants in the big lake
Hot- clear- sunny day.  SW win d with a chop on the lake.  One of our Secchi readings was 26 feet-a record!
It has been a cool- late spring with lots of snow melt and spring rains; With Memorial day weekend there has been lots of boat traffic; lake looks pretty good for early in  the year.
Sunny warm day; lake has a slight chop; looks good!
Nice day today (80s) but we have had lots of rain-a very wet June.  Slight chop on the lake.
Ver windy and choppy; lots of algae; water looks cloudy; 'bad lake day.'
Overcast; it has been windy; choppy with South wind- 10-15mph.
Not a good day for monitoring-too choppy and mostly cloudy.  The lake looks better; I think if it were calm and sunny we would get much better readings.
East wind- choppy and overcast-not a perfect day for monitoring but the lake looks much better.  Maybe it was all the runoff from the June rains that caused the problems.
Sun is in and out; East breeze; choppy but no white caps
Overcast sky; warm days and cool nights; feels like we are moving into a fall pattern; light chop on the lake.
Light wind; low 80s; rain is coming;  lake looks great.
Nice day today (80s) but we have had lots of rain-a very wet June.  Slight chop on the lake. Nice day today (80s) but we have had lots of rain-a very wet June.  Slight chop on the lake.
In the 80s today; been very hot; had a big wind storm 7/20 lake looks green with algae
Mostly cloudy day with a slight wind and 'ripely chop'; lake just doesn't look its marvelous self.
Clear sky; light SE breeze; no rain for 7 days; this has been the longest dry stretch this summer
Sunny day today; very stormy last night; calm lake today. Sunny day today; very stormy last night; calm lake today.  The lake looks much better than the readings reflect-algae bloom coming??????

Pretty nice day; calm; partly cloudy; warm; had lots of stormy weather this week with a lot of rain.  Maybe the run off this week has hit the lake hard--the readings are not up to Deer Lake's potential at all. Pretty nice day; calm; partly cloudy; warm; had lots of stormy weather this week with a lot of rain.  Maybe the run off this week has hit the lake hard--the readings are not up to Deer Lake's potential at all.
partly cloudy partly cloudy partly cloudy partly cloudy
